caption.title: Neighbor joining tree of ZIKV complete genome sequences.
caption.p: The tree was obtained using the best fitting nucleotide substitution model (TN93+G) selected by a hierarchical likelihood ratio test. Branches are drawn to scale in nucleotide substitutions per site according to the bar at the bottom of the tree. Significant posterior probability support (pâ‰¥ 0.9) is indicated by the number along the branch. The Haiti sequence is in bold.
